driver's license, because

00:17:59.080 --> 00:18:01.730
evidence suggests that people
under 16 are going to be

00:18:01.730 --> 00:18:03.000
irresponsible and get
into an accident.

00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:05.120
We discriminate against people
under 21 and say they can't

00:18:05.120 --> 00:18:07.020
drink, because evidence
suggests they'll be

00:18:07.020 --> 00:18:08.950
irresponsible and get into
some kind of trouble.

00:18:08.950 --> 00:18:09.850
We discriminate against--

00:18:09.850 --> 00:18:10.930
BRENDON AYANBADEJO: They
can go to war, though.

00:18:10.930 --> 00:18:11.290
SCOTT FUJITA: Yeah, right.

00:18:11.290 --> 00:18:12.020
They can go to war.

00:18:12.020 --> 00:18:14.220
We discriminate others who get
to a certain age and say they

00:18:14.220 --> 00:18:16.510
can no longer drive, because
evidence suggests that they'll

00:18:16.510 --> 00:18:17.800
be a hazard on the road.

00:18:17.800 --> 00:18:20.680
So again, there is no evidence
to suggest that this will be

00:18:20.680 --> 00:18:22.470
dangerous or harmful
to society.

00:18:22.470 --> 00:18:25.850
It's just about rights, as
Brendon always says.

00:18:25.850 --> 00:18:27.520
FEMALE SPEAKER: Chris, I have a
follow-up question for you,

00:18:27.520 --> 00:18:28.900
if you're comfortable
answering it.

00:18:28.900 --> 00:18:29.120
CHRIS KLUWE: Sure.

00:18:29.120 --> 00:18:31.000
FEMALE SPEAKER: One of your
former teammates, Adrian

00:18:31.000 --> 00:18:33.210
Peterson, recently came out--

00:18:33.210 --> 00:18:35.240
"came out" is probably the
wrong way of putting it--

00:18:35.240 --> 00:18:36.450
[LAUGHTER]

00:18:36.450 --> 00:18:36.940
FEMALE SPEAKER: --on
the radio--

00:18:36.940 --> 00:18:37.640
BRENDON AYANBADEJO: Yeah,
that's wrong.

00:18:37.640 --> 00:18:40.900
FEMALE SPEAKER: He made a
statement, something to the

00:18:40.900 --> 00:18:43.570
effect of, "I'm not with gay
marriage." And then he

00:18:43.570 --> 00:18:46.500
clarified it, later, by saying
he was OK if other people were

00:18:46.500 --> 00:18:48.240
in favor, but he wasn't.

00:18:48.240 --> 00:18:50.640
Have you talked to him
about that at all?

00:18:50.640 --> 00:18:51.640
CHRIS KLUWE: I haven't
talked to Adrian,

00:18:51.640 --> 00:18:52.670
recently, about that.

00:18:52.670 --> 00:18:54.300
We were good friends
in the locker room.

00:18:54.300 --> 00:18:58.870
And for me, the fact that Adrian
is willing to let other

00:18:58.870 --> 00:19:01.110
people have their rights-- while
that's not the ideal

00:19:01.110 --> 00:19:04.860
situation, it's, really, the
best we can hope for from a

00:19:04.860 --> 00:19:07.820
lot of people is the fact that
as long as you're not

00:19:07.820 --> 00:19:10.890
discriminating against people,
you don't have to actually

00:19:10.890 --> 00:19:11.410
embrace it.

00:19:11.410 --> 00:19:13.090
You know, we would like to get
the point where everyone is

00:19:13.090 --> 00:19:15.110
embracing the idea that you
treat other people the way

00:19:15.110 --> 00:19:16.180
you'd like to be treated.

00:19:16.180 --> 00:19:19.450
But while we're working towards
that, avoiding active

00:19:19.450 --> 00:19:22.790
discrimination is one of the
steps to that process.

00:19:22.790 --> 00:19:26.570
And so with Adrian, he may not,
personally, agree with

00:19:26.570 --> 00:19:27.240
same sex marriage.

00:19:27.240 --> 00:19:29.960
He may not, personally, agree
for gay rights, but he's not,

00:19:29.960 --> 00:19:33.490
actively, going out his way
to rally against it.

00:19:33.490 --> 00:19:36.610
And that's something
that I would

00:19:36.610 --> 00:19:38.100
like to see him embrace--

00:19:38.100 --> 00:19:42.050
gay rights-- because it's
human rights, something

00:19:42.050 --> 00:19:42.710
everyone should have,

00:19:42.710 --> 00:19:45.870
But at the end of the day, I'm
not going to crucify him for

00:19:45.870 --> 00:19:48.160
being who he is, being raised
in the environment that

00:19:48.160 --> 00:19:49.280
he was raised in.

00:19:49.280 --> 00:19:52.390
And you know, even saying what
he said, that can be tough to

00:19:52.390 --> 00:19:54.320
do if you raised in a very
religious environment.

00:19:54.320 --> 00:19:57.260
So I'm not upset at Adrian.

00:19:57.260 --> 00:19:59.830
I would wish he would he could
do more, but at the same time,

00:19:59.830 --> 00:20:05.700
he's not actively trying to
conspire against LGBT rights.

00:20:05.700 --> 00:20:06.080
FEMALE SPEAKER: Right.

00:20:06.080 --> 00:20:08.016
CHRIS KLUWE: If that makes
sense to anyone.

