00:20:11.490 --> 00:20:14.750
BRENDON AYANBADEJO: Yes, so
Athlete Ally is a group that

00:20:14.750 --> 00:20:18.620
tries to foster inclusion
of the LGBT

00:20:18.620 --> 00:20:20.050
community into sports.

00:20:20.050 --> 00:20:22.520
So we go around, and we speak
at different schools.

00:20:22.520 --> 00:20:26.400
And we just talk about
LGBT sensitivity.

00:20:26.400 --> 00:20:28.396
The last thing we want is--

00:20:28.396 --> 00:20:30.520
you know, imagine Greg Louganis,
if he didn't

00:20:30.520 --> 00:20:32.850
continue to be the greatest
American diver in history--

00:20:32.850 --> 00:20:34.570
and he's one of my role models
and one of my heroes.

00:20:34.570 --> 00:20:37.700
But imagine if he got bullied
out of diving, because there

00:20:37.700 --> 00:20:40.510
were some straight kids, and
they made fun of him, because

00:20:40.510 --> 00:20:42.350
he was a part of the
LGBT community.

00:20:42.350 --> 00:20:44.840
So we want to foster kids.

00:20:44.840 --> 00:20:47.060
And we want to encourage them
to continue to play sports,

00:20:47.060 --> 00:20:49.200
especially with all the problems
we have with heart

00:20:49.200 --> 00:20:52.950
disease and diabetes and people
being so sedentary.

00:20:52.950 --> 00:20:55.580
The last thing we want to see is
our children being bullied

00:20:55.580 --> 00:20:56.120
out of sports.

00:20:56.120 --> 00:21:00.780
And so I think once you see
somebody like Jason Collins--

00:21:00.780 --> 00:21:03.620
on that level, 7 foot tall
black dude that's gay--

00:21:03.620 --> 00:21:05.730
it destroys a lot of people's
perception of what

00:21:05.730 --> 00:21:06.840
they think gay is.

00:21:06.840 --> 00:21:09.220
And now, oh my god, there's
an athlete in the

00:21:09.220 --> 00:21:10.120
NBA, and he's gay.

00:21:10.120 --> 00:21:12.860
And there's Chris Kluwe and
Scott Fujita, and they're

00:21:12.860 --> 00:21:14.270
straight guys, and they believe
in me, and they

00:21:14.270 --> 00:21:15.080
support me.

00:21:15.080 --> 00:21:17.980
So we think we can do so much
in helping young people,

00:21:17.980 --> 00:21:21.720
curbing suicide rates, letting
kids stand a little bit taller

00:21:21.720 --> 00:21:24.100
that are part of the
LGBT community--

00:21:24.100 --> 00:21:24.988
gosh darn, it is hard.

00:21:24.988 --> 00:21:27.210
[LAUGHTER]

00:21:27.210 --> 00:21:30.360
BRENDON AYANBADEJO: And we'll
curb suicide rates.

00:21:30.360 --> 00:21:32.560
And kids, ultimately, they'll
get better educations.

00:21:32.560 --> 00:21:34.420
They'll feel better about
themselves, and they'll go on

00:21:34.420 --> 00:21:37.630
to be successful Americans, just
by the littlest thing, a

00:21:37.630 --> 00:21:38.550
little bit of support
and love.

00:21:38.550 --> 00:21:39.780
SCOTT FUJITA: Yeah,
it's about kids.

00:21:39.780 --> 00:21:41.870
It lets them say,
I am not alone.

00:21:41.870 --> 00:21:43.830
And like Brendon said,
it will save lives.

00:21:43.830 --> 00:21:44.810
There's no doubt in my mind.

00:21:44.810 --> 00:21:47.200
Like the young lady who I met
down in the GLAAD awards, it

00:21:47.200 --> 00:21:47.920
will save lives.

00:21:47.920 --> 00:21:50.540
There's no doubt in my
mind about that.

00:21:50.540 --> 00:21:52.300
FEMALE SPEAKER: So you mentioned
Jason Collins.

00:21:52.300 --> 00:21:53.340
I thought it was interesting.

00:21:53.340 --> 00:21:57.240
In your brief to the US Supreme
Court, you have the

00:21:57.240 --> 00:22:00.710
