00:22:35.320 --> 00:22:36.930
And backstory, you don't
hear about it.

00:22:36.930 --> 00:22:39.780
That's where we're trying to
get with the male athletes.

00:22:39.780 --> 00:22:41.110
We want it to be a backstory.

00:22:41.110 --> 00:22:42.940
We don't want it to be first
page of "Sports Illustrated,"

00:22:42.940 --> 00:22:44.070
everybody's looking at it.

00:22:44.070 --> 00:22:46.100
It's the biggest talk, and
it's a whole big deal.

00:22:46.100 --> 00:22:47.710
Obama, Oprah--

00:22:47.710 --> 00:22:49.295
I mean that's great, we
want the support.

00:22:49.295 --> 00:22:52.320
But at the same time, we just
want people to be who they are

00:22:52.320 --> 00:22:53.740
and to live their lives
and to be happy.

00:22:53.740 --> 00:22:57.160
So Jason's going to do so much
for people, and he's going to

00:22:57.160 --> 00:22:58.270
continue to work.

00:22:58.270 --> 00:23:01.140
And it'll be, really, great to
see him, actually, play in a

00:23:01.140 --> 00:23:02.580
game next year.

00:23:02.580 --> 00:23:03.320
I don't know if happens.

00:23:03.320 --> 00:23:06.880
And hopefully, if he does play
in a game, it'll be for the

00:23:06.880 --> 00:23:09.550
right reasons, because a
basketball team needs him, not

00:23:09.550 --> 00:23:11.420
because a basketball team
is trying to have a gay

00:23:11.420 --> 00:23:12.530
athlete on a team.

00:23:12.530 --> 00:23:14.090
So I think it's amazing.

00:23:14.090 --> 00:23:17.700
And it, just, shows how far
we've come in such a short

00:23:17.700 --> 00:23:21.600
amount of time, and it really
makes me feel bad for people

00:23:21.600 --> 00:23:25.650
like Martina Navratilova or
Billy Bean or Esera Tuaolo.

00:23:25.650 --> 00:23:28.410
These are all athletes that came
out in the '80s and '90s.

00:23:28.410 --> 00:23:30.080
And now today, this
is being embraced.

00:23:30.080 --> 00:23:31.760
And they lost endorsements.

00:23:31.760 --> 00:23:34.970
They couldn't play in
tournaments, and they tried to

00:23:34.970 --> 00:23:36.970
cover up stories and scandals.

00:23:36.970 --> 00:23:39.470
And you know, it used
to be a sin.

00:23:39.470 --> 00:23:42.110
They were considered sodomites
and all these crazy things.

00:23:42.110 --> 00:23:45.360
And now today, we get to have
someone that's touted as a

00:23:45.360 --> 00:23:48.020
hero, in large part,
because of the

00:23:48.020 --> 00:23:49.660
people that came before.

00:23:49.660 --> 00:23:50.620
SCOTT FUJITA: Yeah, while
it's great to have this

00:23:50.620 --> 00:23:52.470
conversation, I think it'll be
even greater when we get to

00:23:52.470 --> 00:23:53.800
the point where this
conversation

00:23:53.800 --> 00:23:55.040
doesn't need to be had.

00:23:55.040 --> 00:23:57.340
I mean you know, how great
of a deal would that be.

00:23:57.340 --> 00:24:00.930
CHRIS KLUWE: Yeah, and really,
it comes down we're athletes.

00:24:00.930 --> 00:24:01.620
We're playing a sport.

00:24:01.620 --> 00:24:04.280
It shouldn't matter what your
sexuality is, because we're

00:24:04.280 --> 00:24:07.170
out there to do our jobs to the
best of our abilities, and

00:24:07.170 --> 00:24:09.570
sexuality plays no part in that,
except if you're forced

00:24:09.570 --> 00:24:11.700
to cover it up, and you can't
play to the best your

00:24:11.700 --> 00:24:13.580
abilities, because you're
worried about being revealed.

00:24:13.580 --> 00:24:16.690
So that's why what Jason
is doing is so great.

00:24:16.690 --> 00:24:18.420
He's, like, look, I'm not going
to have to deal with

00:24:18.420 --> 00:24:19.500
this anymore.

00:24:19.500 --> 00:24:21.800
Now I'm just going to focus
solely on playing basketball.

00:24:21.800 --> 00:24:24.370
And that's awesome, because
that's what everyone should be

00:24:24.370 --> 00:24:26.030
able to do.

00:24:26.030 --> 00:24:28.070
FEMALE SPEAKER: Did any of
you guys have negative

00:24:28.070 --> 00:24:31.520
repercussions from your teams
for being outspoken in favor

00:24:31.520 --> 00:24:33.770
of equality?

00:24:33.770 --> 00:24:34.440
SCOTT FUJITA: Talk
to this one.

00:24:34.440 --> 00:24:36.194
FEMALE SPEAKER: I though Chris
might want to answer this.

00:24:36.194 --> 00:24:37.628
BRENDON AYANBADEJO:
Stop the presses.

00:24:37.628 --> 00:24:38.106
[LAUGHTER]

00:24:38.106 --> 00:24:40.020
CHRIS KLUWE: Oh boy.

00:24:40.020 --> 00:24:41.882
I'm happy to be with
Oakland right now.

00:24:41.882 --> 00:24:47.190
[LAUGHTER AND APPLAUSE]

00:24:47.190 --> 00:24:48.450
CHRIS KLUWE: Yeah, well
I mean, it is

00:24:48.450 --> 00:24:49.120
one of those things.

00:24:49.120 --> 00:24:52.170
It's unfortunate, in the NFL,
