that people can use as a

00:42:51.660 --> 00:42:55.390
resource for coaches, in that
there is a right way to coach,

00:42:55.390 --> 00:42:59.350
and you don't have denigrate the
kids under your power in

00:42:59.350 --> 00:43:00.170
order to coach well.

00:43:00.170 --> 00:43:03.460
Because that, ultimately,
doesn't teach anyone anything

00:43:03.460 --> 00:43:04.490
useful in life.

00:43:04.490 --> 00:43:06.430
It teaches you to scream at
people, that's about it.

00:43:06.430 --> 00:43:07.820
So he's working on that.

00:43:07.820 --> 00:43:10.440
He's been asking my advice on
kind of, OK, how do I go about

00:43:10.440 --> 00:43:12.050
approaching this
and what to do.

00:43:12.050 --> 00:43:14.870
And hopefully, he'll be able
to kind of parlay that into

00:43:14.870 --> 00:43:17.220
something that people pay
attention to and listen to,

00:43:17.220 --> 00:43:19.540
because coaches are a very
important role model,

00:43:19.540 --> 00:43:20.560
especially for young kids.

00:43:20.560 --> 00:43:21.700
You know, a lot of your
behavior you pick

00:43:21.700 --> 00:43:23.050
up from your coach.

00:43:23.050 --> 00:43:25.460
I think he's doing a great
thing, and I fully plan on

00:43:25.460 --> 00:43:28.540
supporting him in getting that
message out, that bullying is

00:43:28.540 --> 00:43:30.500
not acceptable, whether
it's player to

00:43:30.500 --> 00:43:32.830
player or coach to player.

00:43:32.830 --> 00:43:35.530
BRENDON AYANBADEJO: For me, I
like to talk to the parents

00:43:35.530 --> 00:43:37.320
and educate the parents.

00:43:37.320 --> 00:43:39.800
Before you have your child on
a team, you should talk to

00:43:39.800 --> 00:43:40.220
that coach.

00:43:40.220 --> 00:43:44.830
You should feel out that coach
and let him know that you're

00:43:44.830 --> 00:43:48.060
not going to put up with any
type of discrimination on any

00:43:48.060 --> 00:43:50.190
sports teams that your
children play on.

00:43:50.190 --> 00:43:55.510
And that also opens up the
conversation to their children

00:43:55.510 --> 00:43:58.370
and having this conversation
with their children about LGBT

00:43:58.370 --> 00:44:01.180
rights and LGBT inclusion.

00:44:01.180 --> 00:44:03.430
So when you have those
tough conversations--

00:44:03.430 --> 00:44:05.220
and maybe I'm preaching
to the wrong crowd.

00:44:05.220 --> 00:44:10.500
Usually, I'm talking to straight
people or sometimes

00:44:10.500 --> 00:44:14.420
even LGBT people, but it really
doesn't have to address

00:44:14.420 --> 00:44:16.870
them in this issue on how to
talk about inclusion, because

00:44:16.870 --> 00:44:17.840
they already do.

00:44:17.840 --> 00:44:21.920
So you have to bring up tough
issues like molestation or

00:44:21.920 --> 00:44:25.400
bullying or LGBT awareness
and letting

00:44:25.400 --> 00:44:26.180
your kids be sensitive.

00:44:26.180 --> 00:44:28.220
That's exactly why my kids
are here, today.

00:44:28.220 --> 00:44:30.220
I want them to be around
the LGBT community.

00:44:30.220 --> 00:44:32.690
I brought them to a black tie
event last night, and they

00:44:32.690 --> 00:44:33.760
were freakin' atrocious--

00:44:33.760 --> 00:44:35.400
[LAUGHTER]

00:44:35.400 --> 00:44:36.310
BRENDON AYANBADEJO:
--and screaming.

00:44:36.310 --> 00:44:37.720
But I try to tell them--

00:44:37.720 --> 00:44:42.150
I want my kids to be around the
smartest, the brightest,

00:44:42.150 --> 00:44:44.520
the best people in the world,
and we all know that that

00:44:44.520 --> 00:44:46.180
comes from the LGBT community.

00:44:46.180 --> 00:44:47.550
That comes from society.

00:44:47.550 --> 00:44:49.000
So it opens the door.

00:44:49.000 --> 00:44:50.210
I talk to the parents.

00:44:50.210 --> 00:44:53.400
I tell them, you know, exactly
what you should expect from

00:44:53.400 --> 00:44:56.350
your coaches and what you will
not put up and tolerate with.

00:44:56.350 --> 00:44:59.000
And then have the conversation
with your children, as well,

00:44:59.000 --> 00:45:02.368
about some of these other
tough issues.

00:45:02.368 --> 00:45:03.943
SCOTT FUJITA: Well said, guys.

00:45:03.943 --> 00:45:04.890
[LAUGHTER]

00:45:04.890 --> 00:45:05.505
SCOTT FUJITA: It's
