00:46:50.230 --> 00:46:52.290
that's why it's a big deal that
Jason Collins comes out.

00:46:52.290 --> 00:46:54.650
It shouldn't be, but it's
something that's never

00:46:54.650 --> 00:46:58.370
happened before, and how else
are they going to change

00:46:58.370 --> 00:47:01.530
things, unless they get allies,
unless they get the

00:47:01.530 --> 00:47:05.220
majority of the population to
believe in their cause, which

00:47:05.220 --> 00:47:09.690
is kind of crazy to me that we
even vote for this, that it's

00:47:09.690 --> 00:47:12.610
even up to popular opinion.

00:47:12.610 --> 00:47:15.160
So I just try to explain to
them, what would you do?

00:47:15.160 --> 00:47:17.320
I mean, what did Martin
Luther King do?

00:47:17.320 --> 00:47:18.560
What did Rosa Parks do?

00:47:18.560 --> 00:47:20.990
They screamed for
attention, and

00:47:20.990 --> 00:47:22.040
eventually, things changed.

00:47:22.040 --> 00:47:23.930
And the LGBT community
is no different.

00:47:23.930 --> 00:47:24.930
SCOTT FUJITA: Yeah, change
can be slow.

00:47:24.930 --> 00:47:27.960
At the time of Loving versus
Virginia, I think only 13% of

00:47:27.960 --> 00:47:31.130
the country was on board with
interracial marriage.

00:47:31.130 --> 00:47:33.620
It wasn't until, I think, 1990
that at least a simple

00:47:33.620 --> 00:47:35.070
majority of this country
was on board

00:47:35.070 --> 00:47:36.340
with interracial marriage.

00:47:36.340 --> 00:47:39.000
That's 1990, so change
is slow.

00:47:39.000 --> 00:47:41.750
And it can't get at the
whims of the voter.

00:47:41.750 --> 00:47:43.910
The fact that we're voting on
something like marriage

00:47:43.910 --> 00:47:45.190
equality makes no sense to me.

00:47:45.190 --> 00:47:46.410
I mean, you can't follow
the whims of the

00:47:46.410 --> 00:47:48.800
voter, the mob mentality.

00:47:48.800 --> 00:47:49.930
It's got be the government.

00:47:49.930 --> 00:47:51.190
Brendon said that earlier.

00:47:51.190 --> 00:47:51.690
BRENDON AYANBADEJO:
And I tell guys--

00:47:51.690 --> 00:47:54.800
I'm like, there's countries
where they practice genital

00:47:54.800 --> 00:47:55.400
mutilation.

00:47:55.400 --> 00:47:58.480
There are societies where they
ate people and sacrifice them

00:47:58.480 --> 00:48:00.490
to the gods, and that's because
that was the popular

00:48:00.490 --> 00:48:01.030
thing to do.

00:48:01.030 --> 00:48:02.590
That's what they thought was
the right thing to do.

00:48:02.590 --> 00:48:04.170
So it's no different today.

00:48:04.170 --> 00:48:07.720
I mean, we think we're
civilized, and we claim to be

00:48:07.720 --> 00:48:13.100
the greatest country in
civilization, ever, but yet

00:48:13.100 --> 00:48:15.360
our neighbors in Mexico and our
neighbors in Canada, they

00:48:15.360 --> 00:48:18.030
have marriage equality.

00:48:18.030 --> 00:48:21.060
So I just try to educate guys
and let them know this is why

00:48:21.060 --> 00:48:21.580
it's like this.

00:48:21.580 --> 00:48:22.860
We have to make a change.

00:48:22.860 --> 00:48:24.850
There's people that are
yearning, begging to be

00:48:24.850 --> 00:48:27.400
treated equally, and we're
not doing that.

00:48:27.400 --> 00:48:30.210
And that's what America was
founded on, and quite frankly,

00:48:30.210 --> 00:48:32.765
the Constitution is not living
up to it's end of the bargain.

00:48:32.765 --> 00:48:34.960
So I let them know.

00:48:34.960 --> 00:48:41.520
FEMALE SPEAKER: So the question
is, essentially, does

00:48:41.520 --> 00:48:46.160
there need to be education for
gay people about whether

00:48:46.160 --> 00:48:50.420
athletes who use terms that
are viewed as hostile are

00:48:50.420 --> 00:48:52.970
really hostile toward
the gay community.

00:48:52.970 --> 00:48:55.360
BRENDON AYANBADEJO: I think we
saw, just last week, with Roy

00:48:55.360 --> 00:48:58.130
Hibbert-- are you guys familiar
with the young man

00:48:58.130 --> 00:48:59.850
from the Pacers?

00:48:59.850 --> 00:49:04.350
